<dl id="n53122aa"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53122aa">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53122aa"> 122(aa)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> s. Rahoula, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122aa"><li>FW 60.05 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n53122aa">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n53122aa">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122aa">MS BL 47476b-178</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:377 <a name="cd10" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n53122aa">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Or, la belle Gop&acirc; donna au prince <mark>un fils, qui re&ccedil;ut le nom de R&acirc;houla</mark>. Et le roi &Ccedil;ouddhodana vit avec joie que sa race se continuait, et, comme il avait &eacute;t&eacute; fier de la naissance de son fils, il fut fier de la naissance de son petit-fils. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 39</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Prince Siddharta was happy with his consort Gopa and she bore him a son, Rahoula. For thirteen years he lived thus, happy with his wife, palaces and pleasures. </mm> </dd></dl>
